DESCRIPTION
TestDriftGuard's expectedCommands list in cmd/gen-docs/main_test.go is hand-maintained and silently OMITS shipped CLI pages (etude_retro.md, etude_retro_capture.md, etude_capture-gate.md, and now etude_retro_list.md/etude_retro_show.md unless added). Effect: go test ./... does NOT catch docs staleness for those commands; only make docs-check (full diff) does. Fix: derive the expected page set from the actual generated output (or from the cobra command tree) so the guard can't drift as commands are added. Surfaced during etude-8t4's plan gate (Opus seat). Dogfood/dev-tooling, not product.

DESIGN
## Plan

**Approach:** Make the drift guard derive its checked set from the ACTUAL generated output (the cobra tree via the existing run()), not a hand-list. Rewrite TestDriftGuard to: generate into a temp dir, enumerate every generated etude*.md, byte-compare each against docs/cli/, then orphan-check that docs/cli/ has no etude*.md the generator did NOT produce. Remove the hand-maintained expectedCommands slice entirely and fix the two sibling tests that referenced it. Confirmed via temp-dir gen + diff: current committed docs/cli/ is already fully in sync (17 files, byte-identical), so this fix needs NO make docs regen commit and the new guard passes clean. The old hand-list had 14 entries but omits the 3 shipped pages (etude_retro.md, etude_retro_capture.md, etude_capture-gate.md) — that is exactly the completeness hole.

**Files:**
- cmd/gen-docs/main_test.go - rewrite TestDriftGuard (enumerate-generated + byte-compare + orphan-detect via a checkDrift helper); delete expectedCommands var; repurpose TestGeneratesOneFilePerCommand to assert generated set is non-empty and contains anchors (etude.md, etude_run.md) instead of iterating the hand-list; update TestDeterministicOutput (currently iterates expectedCommands) to enumerate generated files instead; leave TestFilesContainSynopsisAndFlags untouched (its own curated content map, not a completeness list — does not depend on expectedCommands). No change to main.go generation logic.

**Tests:**
- checkDrift(generatedDir, committedDir) helper — DIR-ARGS-ONLY, pure function (signature confirmed feasible against main.go: it globs `etude*.md` in generatedDir for the source-of-truth expected set, byte-compares each against committedDir, then globs `etude*.md` in committedDir for orphans; it does NOT hardcode docs/cli). Returns []error (one per offending page) so callers feed it any pair of dirs. Real-tree TestDriftGuard resolves committedDir via findCommittedCliDir() and calls checkDrift(tempGeneratedDir, committedDir), asserting zero errors (current docs/cli/ in sync → passes clean).
- THREE explicit failure-mode sub-tests, each on a TEMP COPY of the committed set (never the real docs/cli), with the generated dir left intact (full set):
  1. committed-missing: generated = full set; committed-temp = full set MINUS one page → checkDrift returns a non-nil error naming that missing page (proves missing-committed detection — NOT orphan detection, because the generated/expected set is left whole).
  2. committed-orphan: generated = full set; committed-temp = full set PLUS a stray etude_bogus.md → checkDrift returns a non-nil error naming etude_bogus.md (proves orphan detection).
  3. byte-stale: generated = full set; committed-temp = full set but one page has CHANGED bytes → checkDrift returns a non-nil error naming that stale page (proves the byte-comparison staleness check fires, not just existence).
  Happy path: generated == committed-temp, all byte-identical → checkDrift returns no errors. Setup builds both temp dirs by running run() into a temp generated dir, copying it to a temp committed dir, then mutating only the committed copy per case.
- Orphan glob scoped to etude*.md to mirror the generator's own scoping (cleanMarkdownFiles/countMarkdownFiles use etude*.md) — docs/cli/ confirmed to contain ONLY 17 generated etude*.md files, no README/index/hidden files, so no whitelist needed.
- TestGeneratesOneFilePerCommand repurposed: assert >0 generated files and presence of etude.md + a known leaf (e.g. etude_run_list.md).
- TestDeterministicOutput: switch from expectedCommands to enumerating dir1's generated files.

**Docs:**
- None. Test/dev-tooling only; no CLI commands added or changed, so generated docs/cli/ is unchanged and no user-facing or planning docs need updating. No built-binary manual test (no product behavior change).

**Risks:** None significant. Self-contained test-only change. Current docs/cli/ is already in sync so the rewritten guard passes immediately. Only watch-item: keep the orphan glob scoped to etude*.md so a future hand-written index in docs/cli/ would not false-positive (matches generator scoping). Tier 2.

